624. 5. Quo die] Foxe's letter (see p. 46) makes it impossible to take these words with Hodie (1. 2); in accord- ance with the punctuation of the MS.

6. Priore] Wm. Salyng or Seiling († 14 March 1520). In Jan. 1485 he was a confrater of the house of Austin canons at Merton in Surrey, but was resident at Oxford for study, pre- sumably in St. Mary’s College (cf. Ep. 106. 9 n.).
